      "description": "How Many Plants utilizes a playful, illustrative aesthetic reminiscent of an artisanal zine or handcrafted journal. The visual system combines a creamy off-white canvas with deep charcoal text and bold, earthy chartreuse accents. Strong, graphic outlines define components and illustrations, imparting a clean yet distinctly analog feel. Typography mixes a custom display serif for headlines with a typewriter-style sans-serif, enhancing the bespoke and approachable mood. The design emphasizes spaciousness, using generous padding and margin to give elements room to breathe.",
      "customSections": [
        {
          "title": "Agent Prompt Guide",
          "content": "Quick Color Reference:\ntext: #222222\nbackground: #f9f5f1\nborder: #222222\naccent: #bfb33b\nprimary action: no distinct CTA color\n\nExample Component Prompts:\n\nNo distinct primary action color was observed; use the extracted neutral button treatments instead of inventing a filled CTA color.\n\n2. Create a section heading: 'Get to know your plants' using Chromatica font, weight 400, size 36px, line-height 0.89, color Inkwell Black (#222222). Margin-bottom 32px.\n\n3. Create a search input field: Transparent background. Text color Inkwell Black (#222222) (Hellenictypewriter). Bottom border Inkwell Black (#222222) 1px solid. Padding 0px vertical, 12px right. No border-radius.\n\n4. Design a 'Plant Guides' navigation link: Chromatica font, weight 400, size 16px, color Inkwell Black (#222222). Active state indicated by a 1px Inkwell Black (#222222) bottom border."
